SENATE BILL 383
F2 6lr2161
HB 1138/25 – APP CF HB 28
By: Senators Watson, Muse, and West
Introduced and read first time: January 27, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Higher Education – Private Career Schools – Advertising
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Secretary of Higher Education to allow certain private
4 career schools to advertise certain information and collect certain contact
5 information before receiving a certificate of approval from the Maryland Higher
6 Education Commission to operate a private career school in the State; and generally
7 relating to private career schools.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
9 Article – Education
10 Section 10–101(a) and (j)
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Education
15 Section 11–212
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Education
21 10–101.
22 (a) In this division the following words have the meanings indicated.
23 (j) “Private career school” means a privately owned and privately operated
24 institution of postsecondary education other than an institution of higher education that
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0383*

2 SENATE BILL 383
1 furnishes or offers to furnish programs, whether or not requiring a payment of tuition or
2 fee, for the purpose of training, retraining, or upgrading individuals for gainful employment
3 as skilled or semiskilled workers or technicians in recognized occupations or in new and
4 emerging occupations.
5 11–212.
6 (A) THE SECRETARY MAY APPROVE A REQUEST FROM AN APPLICANT FOR A
7 PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL TO ADVERTISE AND COLLECT CONTACT INFORMATION
8 FROM POTENTIAL NEW STUDENTS BEFORE THE PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL RECEIVES
9 A CERTIFICATE OF APPROVAL TO OPERATE.
10 (B) A PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL APPROVED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF
11 THIS SECTION:
12 (1) SHALL:
13 (I) ADVERTISE ONLY INFORMATION RELATING TO THE
14 OPENING OF THE PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL, INCLUDING THE ANTICIPATED DATE OF
15 OPENING, PROGRAMS OF INSTRUCTION, AND THE APPLICATION PROCESS; AND
16 (II) INCLUDE, IN ANY ADVERTISEMENT, A DISCLOSURE THAT
17 THE CERTIFICATE OF APPROVAL TO OPERATE THE PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL IS
18 PENDING APPROVAL; AND
19 (2) MAY NOT COLLECT ANY FEES OR ENTER INTO AN ENROLLMENT
20 AGREEMENT WITH POTENTIAL STUDENTS.
21 (C) THE SECRETARY SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS PROVIDING FOR THE
22 PROCESS TO APPROVE A PRIVATE CAREER SCHOOL TO ADVERTISE UNDER THIS
23 SECTION.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
25 1, 2026.

